# CHANGE ME

Show that the distance of any point \(\z_i\in \reals^p\) from a
hyperplane \(\w^T\x -b=0\) (where \(\w\) and \(\x\) are in \(\reals^p\),
and \(b\in \reals\) is a number) is given by
\[
\frac{ \w^T \z_i -b }{|| \w||}.
\]

